CDFglobalAttributes.TEXT: This file includes radio measurements recorded by the STEREO-A/WAVES instrument. Time resolution varies with instrument mode ranging from 15 seconds to 1 minute.
CDFglobalAttributes.Instrument_type:
Radio and Plasma Waves (space)
Electric Fields (space)
CDFglobalAttributes.Rules_of_use: Data provided are publicly available. If used in presentations or publications, please acknowledge STEREO/Waves Investigation (M. Maksimovic and S. D. Bale, PIs). Please read carefully the caveats attached to the data. For reporting purposes, we request bibliography information for any publication, etc., using these data. Please send information on the use of this data to M. Maksimovic and S. D. Bale (PIs).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Wave vector colatitude in the Radial-Tangential-Normal (RTN) system [Data available after 04-May-2007]
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: X axis points from the spacecraft center to Sun, and the Y axis is the cross product of the solar rotational axis and X, and lies in the solar equatorial plane (towards the West limb).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Wave vector azimuth in the Radial-Tangential-Normal (RTN) system [Data available after 04-May-2007]
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: X axis points from the spacecraft center to Sun, and the Y axis is the cross product of the solar rotational axis and X, and lies in the solar equatorial plane (towards the West limb).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Wave vector colatitude in the Heliocentric Inertial (HCI) system [Data available after 04-May-2007]
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Z is the solar north rotational axis, and X is the solar ascending node on the J2000 ecliptic.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Wave vector azimuth in the Heliocentric Inertial (HCI) system [Data available after 04-May-2007]
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Z is the solar north rotational axis, and X is the solar ascending node on the J2000 ecliptic.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Wave vector colatitude in the Heliocentric Earth Ecliptic (HEE) system [Data available after 04-May-2007]
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: X is the Sun-Earth line, and Z is the north pole for the ecliptic of date.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Wave vector azimuth in the Heliocentric Earth Ecliptic (HEE) system [Data available after 04-May-2007]
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: X is the Sun-Earth line, and Z is the north pole for the ecliptic of date.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Wave vector colatitude in the Heliocentric Earth Equatorial (HEEQ) system [Data available after 04-May-2007]
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Z is the solar rotation axis, and X is in the plane containing the Z axis and Earth, at the intersection of the solar central meridian, and the heliographic equator. When converted to longitude and latitude, this is known as Stonyhurst heliographic coordinates.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Wave vector azimuth in the Heliocentric Earth Equatorial (HEEQ) system [Data available after 04-May-2007]
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Z is the solar rotation axis, and X is in the plane containing the Z axis and Earth, at the intersection of the solar central meridian, and the heliographic equator. When converted to longitude and latitude, this is known as Stonyhurst heliographic coordinates.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: STEREO spacecraft position in the Heliocentric Inertial (HCI) system in km
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Also called Ecliptic J2000. Z is the solar north rotational axis, and X is the solar ascending node on the J2000 ecliptic.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: STEREO spacecraft position in the Heliocentric Earth Ecliptic (HEE) system in km
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: X is the Sun-Earth line, and Z is the north pole for the ecliptic of date.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: STEREO spacecraft position in the Heliocentric Earth Equatorial (HEEQ) system in km
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Z is the solar rotation axis, and X is in the plane containing the Z axis and Earth, at the intersection of the solar central meridian, and the heliographic equator. When converted to longitude and latitude, this is known as Stonyhurst heliographic coordinates.
